* From behind her cape she peered, through the ash that had collected in the 
air around her.
There were sounds of battle out there in the ash, charge blasts lighting it 
up from every direction.
A shuttle had crashed her senses told her, stanting up and shaking the ash 
off her armor that was collecting there.
It was time to get down to some work.*
